In order to compile, you copy the Makefile and generate_grf.f
to a directory of your choice and type 

make generate_grf

This will find the grf.c routine in /u/postdoc/russ/random_field/
and the libraries in /u/postdoc/russ/random_field/FF/ and
/u/postdoc/russ/random_field/gaussian/LIB/

Then run generate_grf:

./generate_grf

Currently, the routine prints out three columns:
 the row of the gaussian random field
 the column of the gaussian random field
 the value of the gaussian random field at that row/column
 ...and a DONE message with the return value (with a # at the front)

When you make changes to generate_grf.f, you need to

make clean
...then...
make generate_grf

Right now the gaussian random field routines are tuned 
to accept an array of 400000 random numbers for every
40 row -by- 64 column gaussian field.

There is a return value which should equal zero.
If the routine crashes (if rows or columns are changed)
then it may do so silently or it may throw a SEGFAULT.

